Six people were injured after two vehicles collided on the M13 Durban-bound near Everton Rd in the Gillits area on Saturday evening (6 May).Just after 11.30pm Rescue Care Paramedics arrived at the chaotic scene where two vehicles collided on the freeway before one of the vehicles left the roadway rolling down an embankment coming to rest on its side. Paramedics found that one of the drivers was entrapped in his vehicle and paramedics, together with the Durban Fire Department worked to free the driver, stabilizing him, said operations director Garrith Jamieson. Five people in the second car sustained serious injuries. Police are investigating the cause of the accident.